Having a look at the implementation of [`drawShape`](https://octave.sourceforge.io/geometry/function/drawShape.html), e.g. by using `edit drawShape`, we see, that a combination of

* [`circleAsPolygon`](https://octave.sourceforge.io/geometry/function/circleAsPolygon.html), 
* [`drawPolygon`](https://octave.sourceforge.io/geometry/function/drawPolygon.html), and
* [`fillPolygon`](https://octave.sourceforge.io/geometry/function/fillolygon.html)

is used, but unfortunately there&#39;s no passing of additional &quot;plot parameters&quot;, like there&#39;s for [`drawCircle`](https://octave.sourceforge.io/geometry/function/drawCircle.html) for example. Latter method doesn&#39;t support filling. So, I&#39;m afraid, for custom color filled circles, we need some indiviual code, like so:

```matlab
% Set up circle parameters
center_x = 0;
center_y = 0;
radius = 1;

% Calculate circle polygon coordinates
nVertices = 72;
coords = circleAsPolygon([center_x, center_y, radius]);

% Draw and fill circle polygon with desired color
drawPolygon(coords(:, 1), coords(:, 2), &#39;c&#39;);
fillPolygon(coords(:, 1), coords(:, 2), &#39;c&#39;);
xlim([-2 2]);
ylim([-2 2]);
axis equal;
```

